+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014WEKYo7fyR2VqdXKoACD22","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to shut down the task queue system in an orderly fashion.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A shutdown operation should signal the system to stop accepting new tasks.\n     8→- After shutdown is initiated, attempting to add new tasks should produce an error.\n     9→- The shutdown should wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish, up to a configurable timeout.\n    10→- If processing tasks do not complete within the timeout, they should be force-cancelled.\n    11→- Callbacks can be registered to run during the shutdown process.\n    12→- The shutdown should produce a summary indicating how many tasks completed, how many were force-cancelled, and how long the shutdown took.\n    13→- Calling shutdown multiple times should be safe and return the same result.\n    14→- If no tasks are processing, shutdown should complete immediately.\n    15→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DR9qbuu4qYaiETXFpdV5Rw","session_id":"fedb1abd-b75b-4c9e-a669-33cc658aaf55","uuid":"5d599374-7d9b-41a4-825a-e317da12d123"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DR9qbuu4qYaiETXFpdV5Rw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the repository structure and contents.\n\n## Complete Repository Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .git/                    (Git repository)\n├── .thunderdome/            (Empty directory)\n├── phases/                  (12 phase requirement files)\n├── src/                     (Source code - currently empty except .gitkeep)\n├── .eslintrc.cjs           (ESLint configuration)\n├── .gitignore              (Git ignore patterns)\n├── .thunderdome-output.jsonl  (Test output)\n├── .thunderdome-stderr.log    (Error log)\n├── TASK.md                 (Main project brief)\n├── package.json            (Project manifest)\n├── package-lock.json       (Dependency lock file)\n├── tsconfig.json           (TypeScript configuration)\n└── vitest.config.ts        (Test framework configuration)\n```\n\n### 2. TASK.md - Project Overview\n\nThe task is to build a **fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch** growing incrementally through 12 phases.\n\n**12 Phases:**\n1. Basic queue - FIFO add/process\n2. Named queues - Multiple independent queues\n3. Priority - Task urgency levels\n4. Delayed tasks - Deferred execution\n5. Retry with backoff - Automatic retry with exponential backoff\n6. Dead letter queue - Failed task storage\n7. Task dependencies - Tasks waiting for other tasks\n8. Concurrency control - Limit concurrent processing\n9. Progress and cancellation - Track progress & abort work\n10. Recurring tasks - Cron-like scheduling\n11. Middleware - Pipeline interceptors\n12. Graceful shutdown - Orderly wind-down\n\n**Key Requirements:**\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- All implementation in `src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies\n- Must compile with `npm run build`\n- Must pass linting with `npm run lint`\n\n### 3. Configuration Files\n\n#### package.json\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### tsconfig.json\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### .eslintrc.cjs\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n#### vitest.config.ts\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n#### .gitignore\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\n### 4. Phase Files - Complete Requirements\n\n#### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Accept payloads and return task objects\n- Each task: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieving next task returns oldest pending, transitions to \"processing\"\n- Return `null` if no tasks available\n- Way to check pending task count\n\n#### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Add tasks to named queues (default queue if omitted)\n- Each queue independent\n- Retrieve from specified queue only\n- Implicit queue creation on first task addition\n- Way to list all queue names\n- Non-existent/empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n#### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1-10 (default 5), 1 is highest\n- Higher priority tasks returned first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Invalid priority values cause error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n#### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Delay in milliseconds or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple simultaneous delays ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task indicates availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n#### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark processing tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks auto re-added with delay if retries remain\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (default 1s, 2s, 4s)\n- Default 3 retries (configurable per task)\n- Base delay 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Exhausted retries = failed state\n\n#### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Tasks with no retries moved to DLQ for their queue\n- Way to view dead-lettered tasks\n- Retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back for fresh retries\n- Way to clear DLQ for a queue\n- Per-queue independent DLQ\n\n#### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can depend on other task IDs\n- Blocked tasks not returned until dependencies complete\n- Circular dependencies detected and rejected at creation\n- Non-existent dependency causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (stay blocked)\n- Way to inspect dependency status\n\n#### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue max concurrency setting\n- Returns `null` if limit reached even if pending tasks exist\n- Completing/failing task frees slot\n- Default unlimited concurrency\n- Way to set/query concurrency limit and active count\n- Works with priority ordering\n\n#### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing tasks report progress 0-100% with optional message\n- Way to query current progress\n- Listeners subscribe to progress updates\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending/processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n#### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule + cron expression + queue + task template\n- Support cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` = every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` = every hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` = every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" for testing\n- Recurring tasks subject to all other rules\n- Removing schedule stops future creation\n\n#### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Middleware registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- No \"next\" call skips processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware errors mark task failed\n- Handler registered per queue after middleware\n- Per-queue independent middleware stacks\n\n#### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown signals stop accepting new tasks\n- New tasks after shutdown error\n- Shutdown waits for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register callbacks during shutdown\n- Summary output: completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe\n- Immediate co